Feature: End-to-End Search and Cart Journey # features/e2e_search_journey.feature:6
  As a signed-in Best Buy user
  I want to search for a product and add it to my cart
  So that I can purchase it
  @e2e @blocker
  Scenario: E2E — Login, search for laptop, add first available item to cart  # features/e2e_search_journey.feature:12
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                                        # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                                   # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    When I login with credentials from test_data                              # features/steps/search_steps.py:121
    Then I should be logged in or continue as guest                           # features/steps/search_steps.py:317
    When I search for the e2e product query                                   # features/steps/search_steps.py:113
    Then the search results page should load                                  # features/steps/search_steps.py:327
    And at least 1 result should be present on page 1                         # features/steps/search_steps.py:340
    When I add the first available item to cart from the results page         # features/steps/search_steps.py:186
    Then the item should be added to cart successfully                        # features/steps/search_steps.py:352

Feature: Best Buy Search Bar # features/search.feature:6
  As a user of Best Buy
  I want to use the search bar to find products
  So that I can browse and purchase items I need
  Background:   # features/search.feature:11

  @positive @critical
  Scenario: TC_POS_01 — Valid product search returns results  # features/search.feature:18
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                        # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                   # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I am on the Best Buy homepage                       # features/steps/search_steps.py:66
    When I search for the "basic_search" product query        # features/steps/search_steps.py:87
    Then the URL should indicate a search results page        # features/steps/search_steps.py:197
    And at least 1 product result should be visible           # features/steps/search_steps.py:207

  @positive @normal
  Scenario: TC_POS_02 — Search result titles match the query keyword           # features/search.feature:25
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                                         # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                                    # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I am on the Best Buy homepage                                        # features/steps/search_steps.py:66
    When I search for the "title_match" product query                          # features/steps/search_steps.py:87
    Then the results page should load successfully                             # features/steps/search_steps.py:216
    And at least 30 percent of result titles should contain a relevant keyword # features/steps/search_steps.py:226

  @positive @minor
  Scenario: TC_POS_03 — Search bar retains the typed query after search  # features/search.feature:32
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                                   # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                              # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I am on the Best Buy homepage                                  # features/steps/search_steps.py:66
    When I search for the "search_bar_retain" product query              # features/steps/search_steps.py:87
    Then the search bar should still display the typed query             # features/steps/search_steps.py:240

  @positive @normal
  Scenario: TC_POS_04 — Gibberish query is handled gracefully       # features/search.feature:38
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                              # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                         # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I am on the Best Buy homepage                             # features/steps/search_steps.py:66
    When I search for the "gibberish" product query                 # features/steps/search_steps.py:87
    Then the site should not show a server error                    # features/steps/search_steps.py:249
    And the site should either show results or a no-results message # features/steps/search_steps.py:260

  @negative @critical
  Scenario: TC_NEG_01 — Invalid login credentials show error message                 # features/search.feature:47
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                                               # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                                          # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I navigate to the Best Buy login page                                      # features/steps/search_steps.py:75
    When I enter invalid login credentials                                           # features/steps/search_steps.py:138
    Then the login should be rejected                                                # features/steps/search_steps.py:282
    And an error message should be shown or the user should remain on the login page # features/steps/search_steps.py:301

  @negative @minor
  Scenario: TC_NEG_02 — Special characters search is handled gracefully  # features/search.feature:54
    Given I open the Best Buy homepage                                   # features/steps/search_steps.py:47
    And the homepage is loaded successfully                              # features/steps/search_steps.py:58
    Given I am on the Best Buy homepage                                  # features/steps/search_steps.py:66
    When I search for the "special_characters" negative query            # features/steps/search_steps.py:100
    Then the site should not show a server error                         # features/steps/search_steps.py:249
    And the search should return zero results or a no-results message    # features/steps/search_steps.py:271

